The code above gets rid of the error message from the console but does not actually overwrite the close function. I don&#39;t think it&#39;s possible to overwrite the function directly, but a workaround is to define a new method, i.e., `customClose` which applies custom code and then closes the dialog. Here&#39;s how it works:

